<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Moves into Wimbledon Tennis Last Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- World number-one Pete Sampras beat
Petr Korda of the Czech Republic to enter the quarter-finals of
the Wimbledon tennis championships on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The set score was 6-4, 6-3, 6-7 (8/10), 6-7 (1/7), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old American now plays Germany's three-times
champion, Boris Becker, for a place in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who hit 27 aces, won the tough battle in three hours
and 21 minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
