<HEADLINE> Bomb Scare at School for Zimbabwean President's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Children at the school attended by
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe's daughter were evacuated this
morning following a bomb hoax, according to Zimbabwe's national
news agency Ziana.
</P>
<P>
Authorities of the Dominican convent school of the Roman
Catholic Church in Harare confirmed the incident to Ziana.
</P>
<P>
"Yes," said one of them, "there was a bomb scare in the
morning when we got a phone call soon after 8:00am that a bomb
has been placed at the school."
</P>
<P>
"We informed police, got children out of the school within
five minutes, and put them at the Herbert Chitepo car park," he
said, adding, "the place was declared safe by police."
</P>
<P>
Eight-year-old Bona, the eldest daughter of President Mugabe
attends the school.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the central intelligence office was also summoned
to the school for investigations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
