<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President's Speech Draws Nationwide Support (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- An inspiring speech made by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin here last night has aroused a high
sense of patriotism throughout the nation.
</P>
<P>
People from all ethnic groups and walks of life have expressed
their belief that China would not have regained Hong Kong so
smoothly if the motherland had not been growing stronger.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a rally here to celebrate Hong Kong's homecoming on
July 1, President Jiang said the unruffled return could ultimately
be attributed to the remarkable achievements of the Chinese people
and the country's increasingly prominent international status.
</P>
<P>
"It is the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party and the
guidance of the Party's basic line that has taken China to
prosperity," a Beijing resident told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"With the guidance of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, we'll concentrate on
economic development, stick to the four cardinal principles, and
continue reform and opening-up," he said.
</P>
<P>
83-year-old Zheng Guochang, a member of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences and professor at Lanzhou University, said two events in
his life have filled him with "pride and joy." One was the
founding of the People's Republic of China in 1949 and the other
was the return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong was the result of the growing strength
of the motherland, said Lin Shouqi, a sixth-generation descendent
of Lin Zexu, regarded in China as a national hero who burnt the
opium confiscated from the British traders before the start of the
Opium War.
</P>
<P>
"The imperialist countries had always tried to have their
figures in the affairs of Tibet when the motherland was weak and
poor," said Cedan Pinco, a Tibetan historian. "It was only until
the peaceful liberation of Tibet in 1951 that we were able to
smash their attempts."
</P>
<P>
History has proved that a powerful and prosperous motherland is
the fundamental guarantee of the unity of the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President's Speech Draws Nationwide Support (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Many people hailed Jiang's remarks that China must persist in
opening up in order to keep up with the progress of the times and
development trends.
</P>
<P>
"His remarks on the need to draw upon the fine fruit of world
civilization by adhering to the policy of reform and opening up
have given voice to our intellectuals' innermost feelings," said
agronomist Yuan Longping, father of hybrid rice.
</P>
<P>
Yan Zhuyin, general manager of a Shanghai-based wool company,
said that it is reform and opening up that helped the firm
introduce advanced technology and management expertise from
overseas -- moves which have also enabled the national economy to
develop rapidly.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinhai, general manager of the Jiangnan Ship Building
Company, said reform and opening-up have made it possible for
the company to sell its products to some 20 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
"It is the reform and opening up that really make a country
prosperous and strong," he said.
</P>
<P>
Many people said that they will carefully review Jiang's
comments on implementing the Party's basic line and following the
road of building socialism with Chinese characteristics charted by
Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhiyang, a railway worker from Henan Province, attributed
the great changes of the nation and the return of Hong Kong
to the adherence to the Party's basic line and Deng's theory.
</P>
<P>
Sun Sigao, a farmer from Shangdong Province, said that the
farmers owed what they are today to the theory about building
socialism advanced by Deng Xiaoping. "Our life will become better
and better so long as we continue along the road charted by Deng
Xiaoping," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
