<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at GMT 1550, July 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS -- France will reflect deeply on its Africa policy, which
is characterized by its military and political alliance with
countries that were formerly French colonies, French Foreign
Minister Hubert Vedrine said today.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov said today
that Hong Kong's return to China was an event of great
significance for both China and the world.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim Fino today turned
down a request by President Sali Berisha to appoint a new interior
minister after the serving incumbent fled the country.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on Wednesday
appointed Sergei Stepashin Justice Minister of the Russian
Federation and dismissed the former minister, Valentin Kovalyov.
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA -- Thousands of Ugandans have fled their homes in
western Bundibugyo District to eastern Congo as rebels are
terrorizing civilians there, informed sources said today.
