<HEADLINE> Saudi Crown Prince Meets Tajik President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Crown Prince and Deputy
Prime Minister Prince Abdullah Bin Abdel Aziz held talks with
visiting Tajik President Emomali Rahmonov in the western coast
city of Jeddah today.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, the two leaders discussed
means of boosting bilateral relations and the latest developments
in the Islamic world.
</P>
<P>
They focused on opportunities and possibilities to strengthen
bilateral cooperation in the economic field, trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
President Rahmonov arrived in Jeddah Monday on a week-long
official visit to the world's oil producer and exporter.
</P>
<P>
Rahmonov, whose visit aims at promoting ties in various fields
between his country and Saudi Arabia, met Saudi King Fahd Bin
Abdul Aziz Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Saudi businessmen on Tuesday, Rahmonov called on
them to increase trade exchanges with his country and their
investment there.
</P>
<P>
He highlighted the opportunities of pouring in investment in his
country, especially in industrial, agricultural, tourism and real
estate fields. 
</P>
