<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Widow of Deng Xiaoping to Rousing Welcome in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 2 (Xinhua) -- At the Hong Kong handover
ceremony, a respectable woman with greying hair in her 80s came
to the fore among emissaries, both Chinese and foreign. Her name
was Zhuo Lin, widow of the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Deng once said he wished to take a trip to Hong Kong after its
return to the motherland, Deng said on a number of occasions. "I
very much want to take a short walk and stay just for a while even
if I'm in a wheelchair."
</P>
<P>
But Deng, the founder of "one country, two systems" concept,
passed away at the age of 93 in late February before his ardent
aspiration comes true. However, it was Deng who announced to the
world China's firm belief to resume its exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong 18 years ago, and included the concept of "one
country two systems" into the annals of history.
His concept eventually led to Hong Kong's return to China on July
1 while maintaining its capitalist system and way of life,
</P>
<P>
"I have make this trip on behalf of Xiaoping," said Zhuo Lin,
who is here with her children for Hong Kong's handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
As part of her preparations for her trip and make it more
meaningful, Madame Zhuo Lin bought a Hong Kong atlas and read it
repeatedly with great care. She strove to acquaint herself with
this part of the Chinese territory, which had been under the
British colonial rule for 156 years. "It is a great red-letter
event for the entire Chinese nation to resume its exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong and I sincerely hope that the future
for Hong Kong will be still more splendid," she said.
</P>
<P>
As the five-star national rose side by side with regional
bauhinia flag of the Hong Kong SAR at zero hour on July 1, Madame
Zhuo and her children moved to tears. For Zhuo lin, she could
hardly control herself and all sorts of feelings welled up in her
heart.
</P>
<P>
At the inaugural ceremony for the establishment of the HKSAR
government at 10 sharp am on July 1, President Jiang Zemin
descended the rostrum especially to greet and shook hands with
smiling Zhuo, who was then seated at the second row of the rostrum
.
</P>
<P>
During his address at the inaugural ceremony, Tung Chee Hwa,
who was just sworn in as the Chief Executive of the Hong Kong SAR,
said with excitement, "I'm very glad that Madame Zhuo has come,
and we would like to extend her our full respect."
</P>
<P>
At Tung's proposal, the entire hall of the inaugural ceremony
burst into rousing applauses. Zhuo Lin rose and made several bows
to the audience. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali King Stresses Poverty Eradication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Nepali King Birendra said here
today that the Nepali government will prepare concrete programs
focusing on poverty eradication, employment and food security
under the Ninth Five Year Plan (1997-2002).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the joint session of the Nepali parliament, the king
said programs at the grassroots level will be launched in order to
put into practice the concept of balanced development in which
activities related to literacy, clean drinking water, small and
cottage industries, small-scale hydroelectricity development and
universal primary health will complement each other.
</P>
<P>
He said the policy on making villages self-reliant through
programs of village development in accordance with the concept of
"Build Your Village Yourselves" will continue.
</P>
<P>
And the government will make special efforts to uplift the
economic and social conditions of the people living in the most
remote parts of the country, he added.
</P>
<P>
Outlining the government's policies in the fiscal year 1997-98
beginning on July 15, Birendra said development programs will be
implemented to gain high economic growth rate, and the policy of
reducing government involvement in public enterprises and
embracing participation of the private sector will be continued.
</P>
<P>
He said a long-term agricultural development plan will be
implemented by utilizing irrigation, fertilizers, rural
agricultural roads, rural electrification and modern agricultural
technology.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will also implement the policy of
investment promotion by creating a congenial environment for
private sector development and investment.
</P>
<P>
The king noted that his government will launch programs to
directly link production-oriented areas with the commercial sector
in order to reduce trade imbalance.
</P>
<P>
On the development of the country's huge water resources, the
king said a long-term strategy will be prepared in this effort,
and more encouragement will be given to the private sector and
foreign investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
