<HEADLINE> Movie Reception in Mongolia Marks Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese movie reception,
attended by more than 150 high ranking Mongolian officials and
diplomats, was held at the Chinese Embassy here today to celebrate
Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Mongolia Qi Zhijia said China's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Hong on July 1
was a great event in the history of China and international
politics. It proved the correctness of the "one country, two
systems" concept of late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Sanjasuren Zorig, chairman of the Standing Committee of
Political Power Construction of Great Hural; Galsandagva
Nyamdavaa, minister of Infrastructure Development; Chultem
Lhagvajav, minister of Education and Gombosurengyn Damdinsuren,
chief of general staff of the armed forces were among those
attended the reception.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, Qi said Hong Kong's peaceful return not only
was of significance for the unification of China, but also may
serve as a solution to problems left over from the history between
countries.
</P>
<P>
"One country, two systems", "Hong Kong People governing Hong
Kong", and "a high degree of autonomy" were China's policies to
maintain Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We firmly believe that Hong Kong will have a more beautiful
tomorrow," said the Chinese ambassador. 
</P>
</TEXT>
