<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suzhou Expects Increased Agricultural Cooperation With Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The government of Suzhou city in
China's eastern Jiangsu Province has made a list of 40
agricultural development projects for an investment fair to be
held in Hong Kong later this year.
</P>
<P>
The projects include cultivating fine plant and farm animal
seeds; fostering edible fungus; planting and selling of flowers,
fruits, and vegetables; raising quality pigs, rare poultry and
aquatic products; and processing and distribution of farm produce.
</P>
<P>
There are 11 projects each involving investments of more than
five million US dollars. The largest two, which are a pig farm and
a meat processing plant, are worth over 20 million US dollars,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Suzhou has the most developed outside-funded economy in
Jiangsu, one of China's richest provinces. Hong Kong entrepreneurs
are the most active investors here, venturing 8.3 billion US
dollars in over 4,358 projects, which account for 60 percent of
the total outside-investment deals in the city.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong investors are mainly interested in manufacturing
industries such as textiles, pharmaceuticals, machinery,
electronics and telecommunications. 
</P>
