<HEADLINE> Palestinian Youth Killed in Clashes in Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- An 18-year-old Palestinian youth
was shot dead by Israeli soldiers near Morag Jewish settlement in
the Gaza Strip today, according to a report of JMCC, a
Palestinian press service based in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred when Israeli soldiers tried to disperse
Palestinian demonstrators near the settlement.
</P>
<P>
When Ihab Maher Al-Assar and fellow demonstrators tried to
obstruct an Israeli bulldozers moving on a plot of Palestinian
land and threw stones at the soldiers, the troops opened fire in
response. The youth was hit by rubber bullets on the chest and
died of injuries later.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian residents have held protests for days running
against Israeli attempts to confiscate the land for expansion of
the settlement.
</P>
<P>
In the West Bank city of Hebron, Meanwhile, violence ruled
the streets again today. The Israeli army deployed snipers on
the rooftops in the city in an attempt to scare away
Palestinian protesters. They also blocked with cemented barrels
the alley where a home-made explosive charge was thrown at
them Tuesday. Two soldiers were wounded.
</P>
<P>
During today's clashes Palestinian youths tossed Dozens of
petrol bombs along with rocks against the heavily armed
soldiers. No Israeli soldiers were hurt. But seven Palestinian
stone-throwers were wounded by live ammunition and 12 others
by rubber bullets. 
</P>
