<HEADLINE> 6,000 Ethiopian Refugees Return Home from Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 6,000 Ethiopian
refugees have returned home from Sudan through the border town of
Humera in northern Tigray region since late May, the Ethiopian
refugee and returnee affairs authority said here today.
</P>
<P>
The authority said the returnees were given cooking utensils,
blankets, plastic shelters and a nine-month food ration during
their stay at temporary shelters.
</P>
<P>
The returnees were also given money when they reached their
home areas to enable them start normal life, the authority added.
</P>
<P>
According to a tripartite agreement reached between the United
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) and the
governments of Ethiopia and Sudan, 20,000 Ethiopian refugees will
be repatriated from Sudan starting from May 25 of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
