<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims Nine More Lives in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Nine more people died of
cholera in Dar es Salaam last week, bringing the death toll to
163 since the epidemic broke out in the city towards the end of
last January.
</P>
<P>
The city Health Commissioner, Matiku Nyakarungu, told
reporters here today that there were 114 new cholera cases this
week and that by this morning only 30 were still in the city's
hospitals and special camps.
</P>
<P>
Nyakarungu said the disease has so far affected a total of
4,414 people.
</P>
<P>
But he said that the situation is improving after the
government called for healthy living styles among Dar es Salaam
residents.
</P>
<P>
"People should take care of their lives. They should ensure
that they live in clean environment, boil drinking water, use
toilets and take to hospital immediately any person with
suspected cholera," Nyakarungu stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
