<HEADLINE> Photo Show on HK Opens in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- About 200 glossy photos displayed at
an art house here this evening inspired the admiration of many
visitors who came to celebrate the return of Hong Kong to its
motherland China.
</P>
<P>
The photography exhibition that opened this evening at an art
center in the Egyptian Opera House is designed to give a
comprehensive and detailed account of Hong Kong today and
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the picture show, entitled "History and
Development of Hong Kong," was started a year ago, according to
Luo Hansheng, Cultural Attache at the Chinese Embassy, a
co-sponsor of the event.
</P>
<P>
"The exhibit is of a very high level, in photos, presentation
and content," said Mohamed Ghoneim, first under-secretary of state
for foreign cultural relations of Egyptian Ministry of Culture,
who spent over 30 minutes roaming around the exhibition to
appreciate those pictures, with the accompany of Chinese
Ambassador Yang Fuchang.
</P>
<P>
During an interview with Xinhua, the Egyptian official sang
highly of the significance of China's resumption of sovereignty
over its once-lost territory after 156 years of British colonial
rule.
</P>
<P>
Ghoneim said he found a spontaneous overflow of powerful
feelings to say congratulations to the Chinese people on this
glorious occasion.
</P>
<P>
"We consider the occasion a valid and remarkable symbol of the
emancipation of any occupied land that one day the rights will go
to its owners," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We Egyptians and Arabs feel perhaps more than any other
people, if we can say, the sufferings from injustice and
occupation, " he added.
</P>
<P>
Ghoneim hailed the return of Hong Kong as a "glorious day and a
hopeful day for people under occupation to feel hope that one day
through struggle, insistence and persistence that they will gain
their rights back."
</P>
<P>
"Egypt hopes that Hong Kong will join the march of China toward
prosperity, justice, peace and love," said the Egyptian official,
who expressed good wishes on behalf of the Egyptian Ministry of
Culture.
</P>
<P>
The ten-day picture show is co-sponsored by the Egyptian
Ministry of Culture and the Chinese Embassy here. 
</P>
