<HEADLINE> Huge Oil Painting "Festive Day" Sold in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Oil painting artist Liu Yuyi's
huge masterpiece "Festive Day" has been sold at price of 23
million Hong Kong dollars (about 2.9 million US dollars), it was
announced at a press conference held here today.
</P>
<P>
The oil painting, a sister-piece of the artist's another
masterpiece "Festive Evening," was sold to the Hong Kong Parkview
Group Limited.
</P>
<P>
Taking as its theme the return of Hong Kong to China in 1997,
Liu Yuyi, with rich representation and skillful techniques,
portrays in the huge oil painting Chinese leaders Deng Xiaoping,
Jiang Zemin and others joining the massive crowd of people from
the inland areas and Hong Kong to celebrate this historical event.
</P>
<P>
The painting, which took three years to complete, from 1993 to
1997, represents Liu's philosophy of art -- the combination of
reality and romance. Set in the background are images from the
magnificent landscapes of both the inland areas and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yuyi, born in Nanjing in 1940, was settled down in Hong
Kong in 1991. His "Festive Evening" was sold in Hong Kong at a
price of 8.36 Hong Kong dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
