<HEADLINE> Agreement Reached Between IOC, HK Olympic Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- An agreement on the future
identity of Hong Kong athletes taking part in Olympic Games was
reached here today between the International Olympic Committee and
the Amateur Sports Federation and Olympic Committee of Hong Kong
(ASF&AMP;OC).
</P>
<P>
The agreement, signed by IOC President Juan Antonio Samaranch
and ASF&AMP;OC President A. de O. Sales, says, "It is the common aim
to enable the people of Hong Kong to continue taking part in the
Olympic Games and generally in sports competitions everywhere as a
separate and independent entity."
</P>
<P>
The parties agreed that the ASF&AMP;OC will retain its recognition
as an NOC and will function according to the Olympic Charter.
</P>
<P>
In practice, the agreement provides that the Country (China) be
added to the Region "Hong Kong" in the designation of the ASF&AMP;OC;
Hong Kong will fly the flag of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region with a bauhinia in the center at all times.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Chinese National Anthem will be played on
official occasions such as flag-raising and victory ceremonies;
the initials "HKG" will be maintained; and the emblem will feature
the flower Bauhinia with the Five Rings and the Chinese characters
of Hong Kong, China all within a circle followed by "HONG KONG"
with "CHINA" underneath.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch flew to Hong Kong yesterday after a meeting in
Beijing with Chinese Premier Li Peng and Wu Shaozu, minister of
the State Physical Culture and Sports Commission.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Samaranch met with HKSAR Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa and ASF&AMP;OC President A. De O. Sales separately. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
