<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Non-Communist Parties Hail Jiang's Speeches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Central committees of China's eight
non-Communist parties and the All-China Federation of Industry and
Commerce have met over the past few days to discuss Chinese
President Jiang Zemin's three Hong Kong handover speeches made in
Hong Kong and Beijing.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that President Jiang's speeches had declared
clearly the determination of the Chinese government and people to
stick to the socialist road and reunify the country in line with
the principle of "One country, two systems" conceived by late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping and to safeguard regional and world
peace.
</P>
<P>
China now has eight non-Communist parties: the Revolutionary
Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, the China Democratic League,
the China Democratic National Construction Association, the China
Association for Promoting Democracy, the Chinese Peasants and
Workers Democratic Party, the China Zhi Gong Party, the Jiu San
Society, and the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
He Luli, chairman of the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese
Kuomintang, said she believed that the "one country, two systems"
principle applied in Hong Kong has set an example for tackling
Macao and Taiwan issues.
</P>
<P>
He Luli, daughter of a senior Kuomintang official, urged the
Taiwan authorities to treat Jiang's speeches seriously and make
positive responses.
</P>
<P>
Lu Jiaxi, a renowned scientist and chairman of the China
Peasants and Workers Democratic Party, called for greater efforts
to inspire patriotism in the people -- a point Jiang emphasized in
his speeches.
</P>
<P>
"We should strengthen education in patriotism among all the
people, and promote China's traditional virtues to rejuvenate the
country with a practical approach," he said.
</P>
<P>
All non-Communist parties urged their party members to study
Jiang's speeches and turned the encouraging words into action.
</P>
</TEXT>
