<HEADLINE> 23 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-three rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in military
operations staged by the Turkish security forces in southeastern
Turkey, an official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said the Turkish government troops shot dead 15 PKK militants
in Siirt province, four in Diyarbakir province, three in Hakkari
province linking Iran and northern Iraq and one in Bingol province.
</P>
<P>
It said the government troops captured two PKK members and
three people who provided logistic support to the PKK.
</P>
<P>
Six PKK guerrillas surrendered to the Turkish security forces
in Sirnak province, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Over 24,000 people, including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops, have been killed in conflicts since August
1984 when the PKK started a separatist war for autonomy in
eastern and southeastern Turkey. 
</P>
