<HEADLINE> HK's Ties with Home of Terracotta Warriors Closer After Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's state policy to boost the
development of west and central regions will further the economic
cooperation between the province of Shaanxi, home of the ancient
terracotta warriors, and Hong Kong after its return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Andong, governor of this northwest China's province,
recently told Xinhua that Shaanxi is abundant in natural and human
resources. "After the handover, the cooperation between the two
regions can speed up the commercialization of high-tech research
findings in Shaanxi. The province can also give play to Hong
Kong's role as an international trading hub," Cheng said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Hong Kong, regarded as a shopping paradise and the
world's culinary center, can enhance its tourist exchanges with
Shaanxi, which is "not just the home of terracotta warriors but
also the location of many other world-famous places of interest,"
Cheng said.
</P>
<P>
He also predicted that the air route between Xi'an and Hong
Kong will become more popular than ever.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is an international financial hub while Shaanxi is
the regional financial center in northwest China. The financial
exchanges between the two localities in the future can improve the
use of capital market for Shaanxi, "thus presenting a stronger
financial support for the development of the local economy," Cheng
said.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, a total of 1,280 enterprises with Hong
Kong investment had been registered in the province by 1996, with
an aggregate investment of 2.3 billion US dollars. The trade
volume between Shaanxi and Hong Kong hit 800 million dollars last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
