<HEADLINE> HKSAR Passports Begins to Be Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua)-- The passports of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) began to be issued today,
the first working day after the establishment of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
A middle-aged man became the first local citizen receiving the
passport at 9 o'clock this morning in the Immigration Department
of HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
In the hall of the department, people began to line up in early
morning to get their passports from some 20 counters.
</P>
<P>
A 19-year-old girl said that although she has got a British
passport, as a native of Hong Kong, she felt that she should have
a passport of her own country.
</P>
<P>
A man in his 70s said that after Hong Kong's return to China,
Hong Kong people can hold HKSAR passports, which are very
convenient for tourism and business.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong people began to apply for HKSAR passports on June 10
this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
