<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Denies Shooting Dead Villagers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities today denied
that they had shot dead 58 villagers in Shan state of the country
as claimed by the Shan rebels.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said a story by Reuters, entitled "Shan Rebels
Say SLORC Shot Dead 58 Villagers", appeared on July 2 in The
Nation, a Thai newspaper.
</P>
<P>
SLORC is an acronym for Myanmar's ruling State Law and Order
Restoration Council.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar authorities said they believed the insurgents, from
a breakaway group of the former Mong Tai Army (MTA), are
deliberately spreading false information in a bid to cover up a
June 13 incident in which the group ambushed civilians, killing 25
of them and wounding five others.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
