<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao To Establish Special Body to Upgrade Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Macao is to establish a special
committee to help upgrade its traditional industrial sector with
new technology.
</P>
<P>
Today's Macao Daily News quoted Macao Governor Vasco Rocha
Vieira as saying that the government plans to establish a
Technology Reform Committee, which will take charge of making
policy to modernize Macao industry.
</P>
<P>
It said that the governor made this announcement at a two-day
seminar that ended today. But the governor did not elaborate when
the committee will come into being.
</P>
<P>
The proposed committee will be composed of government
departments, representatives of companies and other institutions
related to technology upgrading, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Macao's industrial sector, mainly textile and garment making,
has been challenged by strong competitors from neighboring
regions. Its toy-making industry is dying out.
</P>
<P>
Experts say Macao's industry is in desperate need of
technological upgrade to survive.
</P>
<P>
The governor said he hope the new committee will help local
firms get more access to new technology and data. He also hopes
that more private firms will join in the committee so that it can
work effectively.
</P>
<P>
"Macao is planning many work," he told those attending the
seminar at the University of Macao. "The work includes increase of
contacts with international institutions and the introduction of
new technology. I hope Macao can benefit from it," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
