<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Macao
dropped to 3.5 percent between March and May this year, latest
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that the jobless rate was 0.8 percent down from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The sub-unemployment rate declined to 0.9 percent, comparing
with 1.7 percent in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The highest rate of unemployment hit 4.8 percent in 1996, a
result of a two-year-long sluggish economy.
</P>
<P>
However, the figures dropped from late last year, which local
experts say is a sign of an economic recovery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
