<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Kills 9 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- At least nine people were killed
when a luxury bus plunged into a river in Dhandhuka Taluka
district of Gujarat state of western India today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the bus was carrying over 50
people. Twenty people swam to safety. Nine bodies were found and
the toll could rise as the search for other passengers was still
going on.
</P>
<P>
Local officials and police officers of the district rushed to
the scene to supervise rescue operations.  
</P>
