<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Rain stopped play at Wimbledon again
on Thursday, interrupting the quarter-final between Pete Sampras
and Boris Becker with the American 3-1 up in the first set.
</P>
<P>
On Court One another former champion Michael Stich of Germany
had just won his first service game against home favourite Tim
Henman.
</P>
<P>
Australian doubles specialist Todd Woodbridge was 7-6 2-6 6-0
3-4 up against another German 19-year-old Nicolas Kiefer on Court
Two.
</P>
