<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Session Concluded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The 26th Session of the Standing
Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) concluded
today, with laws on highways and on animal epidemic prevention and
a number of decisions adopted.
</P>
<P>
The today's meeting was presided over by Qiao Shi, chairman of
the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
This was the second time the two laws were presented for
review. They were adopted by the NPC Standing Committee today, and
will go into effect on January 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The Law on Highways consists of 88 articles in nine chapters
with detailed stipulations on highway planning, construction,
maintenance, management, toll, supervision and liabilities. The
Law on Animal Epidemic Prevention includes in its seven chapters
provisions on animal epidemic prevention, disease control and
eradication, and quarantine of animals and animal by-products.
</P>
<P>
At today's meeting, the NPC Standing Committee approved
decisions on the termination of the Preparatory Committee for the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region and on the date for the
election of deputies to people's congresses at the county level.
</P>
<P>
Also approved at the meeting were decisions on joining the
international convention of recalling civil and
commercial testimonies from abroad and on Protocol No. 1 and
Protocol No. 2 to the African Nuclear Weapon-Free Zone treaty.
</P>
<P>
The central final account and the report on the central final
account presented by Finance Minister Liu Zhongli on behalf of the
central government were also adopted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
