<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> RBI Relaxes Foreign Exchange Rules </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 3 (Xinhua)-- The Reserve Bank of India (RBI)
today relaxed the rules for release of foreign exchange for
employment and basic travel quota (BTQ), said an RBI official
release today.
</P>
<P>
The RBI has also enhanced the powers of the authorized dealers
(ADs) in release of foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rules, ADs can release up to 3,000 US dollars per
person towards BTQ for employment and an additional 2,500 US
dollars per person could be released apart from the BTQ
entitlements. ADs can also release up to 1,000 US dollars per
person towards gift to relatives abroad and release the same
amount for donations to organizations abroad.
</P>
<P>
Previously, ADs could only release up to 2,000 US dollars per
person towards BTQ, 500 US dollars per calendar year per person
towards gift, 500 US dollars donation and 500 US dollars per
person or 1,000 US dollars per family for emigration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
