<HEADLINE> India Continues Search Operations for Missing Crew </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- India's coast guards and navy
continued to search for two crew on board the F-27 aircraft of
Elbee Airlines, which was missing after it took off from the
Mumbai (Bombay) airport early today, airport sources said here.
</P>
<P>
"There is still no clue of the crew members of the twin-engine
aircraft which disappeared from the radar screen of the Mumbai Air
Traffic Control (ATC) shortly after taking off for Bangalore," the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
A "Sea King" helicopter of the Indian navy and coast guards
have been pressed into service since early this morning to trace
the missing crew, captain Majumdar and captain Balsara.
</P>
<P>
Bad weather conditions have been hampering the search
operations. This is the second major incident in the last 45 days.
Earlier on May 25, an aircraft called "Dauphin" crashed into the
Arabian Sea while trying to land at the Mumbai airport killing
both the crew members on board.  
</P>
</TEXT>
