<HEADLINE> Chairmen of Six HK Provisional District Boards Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Six out of the 18 Hong Kong
Provisional District Boards each elected a chairman at their
respective meeting today, which was the first gathering since the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC) began its work within Hong
Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Peggy Lam, Lau Wong-fat, Choy Kan-pui, Lam Wai-keung, Cheung
Hok-ming and Mar Yuer-har were elected respectively chairmen of
the Provisional District Boards of Wan Chai, Tuen Myn, Sha Tin,
the Islands, Tai Po and Southern.
</P>
<P>
In her inauguration speech, Peggy Lam said that she was ready
to work hard, lay down her life for her duties, be loyal to the
Basic Law and the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR)
of the People's Republic of China (PRC).
</P>
<P>
She told Xinhua that she will, together with her colleagues,
make efforts to resolve the remaining problems in the next two
years including the environmental protection and traffic troubles
in the Wan Chai district.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the PLC, 12 other Provisional
District Boards will each elect their chairmen respectively on
July 4 and 5.
</P>
<P>
The Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC) stated in August 1993 that the last District Boards
of the London-controlled Hong Kong government should end their
existence by June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
the Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong SAR in February
this year adopted the decision to form the new Provisional
District Boards of the HKSAR and that it was up to the government
of the HKSAR to take charge of making due preparations. In June
this year, the HKSAR Chief Executive's Office announced a namelist
of the members of the Provisional District Boards, and said that
their term would expire at the end of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
