<HEADLINE> First Silk Newspaper Published in Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The "Zhejiang Daily" of East
China's Zhejiang Province, known as "Home of Silk", published
today a collector's edition of its July 1 issue on a piece of silk
as a permanent memory of Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
It took two days to print it. The print is clearer than the
ordinary newsprint edition. It records the Hong Kong handover
ceremony, the official establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region and other events of the day in vivid and
bright colors.
</P>
<P>
It has been collected by the Museum of Chinese History, the
Museum of the Chinese Revolution, the China Silk Museum, Zhejiang
Museum, and the Zhejiang Museum of Natural History. 
</P>
</TEXT>
