<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Outgoing, New Ambassadors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met on
separate occasions with outgoing and new ambassadors from six
countries here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The two outgoing ambassadors to China are Finland's Ilkka
Ristimaki and Kojo Amoo-Gottfried of Ghana.
</P>
<P>
The four new ambassadors are Lucas Pande Tavaya of Zimbabwe,
Nolana Ta-Ama of Togo, Tajikistan's Jamshed Karimov, and Eritrean
Ambassador Tewoldebrhan Woldemikael.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his appreciation for the efforts by the two
outgoing ambassadors to promote relations between China and their
countries.
</P>
<P>
He told the four new ambassadors to make great efforts to
enhance friendship and cooperation between China and their
countries during their terms of office.
</P>
<P>
The six ambassadors all agreed that the return of Hong Kong is
a great event worth celebrating not only by the Chinese but also
the whole world. 
