<HEADLINE> Sweden Calls for Fight Against Juvenile Prostitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Sweden wishs to intensify the
fight against prostitution involving children in the Baltic Sea
region.
</P>
<P>
Sweden Foreign Minister Lena Hjelm-Wallen said this at the
foreign ministers' meeting of the annual Council of the Baltic Sea
States (CBSS) in Riga, Latvia, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The minister proposed that countries involved should jointly
investigate the problem and decide on measures. She said there
were signs that such sexual "trading" involving juveniles was
increasing in the Baltic Sea region.
</P>
<P>
The CBSS is made up of the four Nordic countries plus Estonia,
Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, Russia, Germany and the European
Commission. The ministers will discuss CBSS's future work and
issues such as enlargement and the security policy at the meeting
scheduled to close today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
