<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets German Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng met here
this afternoon with Juergen Sarrazin, chairman of the board of
directors of the Dresdner Bank Group of Germany, the first
financial institution from Germany and Europe to open a branch in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Premier spoke highly of the long-term fruitful cooperation
between China and the German Bank Group and congratulated on the
opening of the Bank's branch in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Li said that, with the growth in economic strength since the
introduction of reform and opening up policy, China's demand for
capital has been rising rapidly. As the biggest developing country
in the world, China does not only need to expand its domestic
financial and capital markets but also need to import a large
amount of foreign capital for economic development.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the hope that the Chinese and German sides would
further strengthen their financial cooperation and that Dresdner
Bank should take an active part in financing China's
infrastructural projects and technical transformation projects of
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The German banker said that his bank has a close business
relationship with its Chinese counterparts, and the opening of the
bank's branch in Beijing will make it more favorable for the bank
to provide good and comprehensive service in financing,
consultation and training.
</P>
<P>
Sarrazin is here as a guest of China's Ministry of Finance.
</P>
</TEXT>
