<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TDC Signs Cooperation Document with Peruvian Counterpart&AMP;0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Trade Development Council
(TDC) marked the first business day of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region with the signing of an agreement with its
Peruvian counterpart to strengthen cooperation between the two
trade promotion agencies in increasing bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement between TDC and the Export Promotion
Commission of Peru (PROMPEX), the TDC and PROMPEX have undertaken
to improve and expand trade and economic ties between Hong Kong
and Peru by regularly exchanging information and views on
expansion of trade and major economic and trade issues.
</P>
<P>
The two agencies will also cooperate and provide mutual
assistance in organizing trade, official or private business
missions, and provide support in the participation and
organization of trade promotions.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's total exports to Peru soared by more than
seven-fold between 1991 and 1996, reaching over 470 million HK
dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months of this year, exports to Peru also
soared 40 percent to reach 152.3 million HK dollars. Major items
are toys, radios, consumer electronics, watches and clocks,
telecommunications equipment, computers, sports shoes, plastic
articles, household electrical appliances and travel goods.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, Hong Kong's imports from Peru registered a
35 percent growth, amounting to 125.3 million HK dollars. Major
imports include copper, zinc, fish and textiles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
