<HEADLINE> Food, Essentials Sent To Sri Lanka's North </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 30,000 tons of food and
other essential items worth 23.1 million US dollars were sent to
Sri Lanka's Northern Jaffna Peninsula during the last three
months, a military spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
The Jaffna Peninsula was once the stronghold of the rebel
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), who have waged a
14-year-old war for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. Government troops recaptured the peninsula in May last
year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, the spokesman said every effort
was made to ensure that the North was adequately supplied without
a break and the authorities in the North are satisfied with the
supply situation.
</P>
<P>
More shipments and lorry loads of goods will be sent to the
North in the coming weeks, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in a gesture of goodwill, the Jaffna Traders
Association has donated 2,300 kilograms of red onions produced in
Jaffna Peninsula for distribution to displaced families in the
North Central Province, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
