<HEADLINE>   Chinese General Chamber of Commerce Marking HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The local Chinese General Chamber
of Commerce held a reception here today to celebrate Hong Kong's
return to China.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), attended the cocktail party with
more than 800 other guests.
</P>
<P>
Also attending were Zhou Nan, director of the Xinhua News
Agency Hong Kong Branch, Ma Yuzhen, commissioner of the Chinese
Ministry of Foreign Affairs in the HKSAR, and Tsang Hin Chi,
president of the CGCC.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said that Hong Kong has returned to the embrace of the
motherland, entering into a new era marked by the "one country,
two systems" and "Hong Kong people governing Hongkong" formula.
</P>
<P>
He said that the inauguration of the HKSAR demonstrates the
central government's full confidence in the Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
He urged all Hong Kong people to become united under the banner
of "loving the country and Hong Kong," and to maintain the
region's social stability and its status as an international
economic and trade center, in order to make a success of
implementing the Basic Law and achieving a high degree of
autonomy.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment 100 years ago, the CGCC has been trying
to unite the local trade and business community for the betterment
of Hong Kong, as well as for the development of the motherland,
according to Tsang.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that it will continue to encourage its members to
invest in the inland areas, back the country's policies on
economic development and exploring the international market, and
work hard for the long-term stability and prosperity of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
