<HEADLINE> Stimulant Drugs Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities today seized
 990,000 tablets of Amphetamine, a kind of stimulant narcotic
drugs, in Kyaing Tong, a border town in the country's eastern Shan
state.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said the tablets were intercepted by the local
law enforcement authorities from a vehicle at a place 32
kilometers north of Kyaing Tong.
</P>
<P>
One person involved was arrested at the scene, while two other
accomplices absconded, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Myanmar authorities also seized 10,000 tablets
of Rama stimulants in Tachilek, the same state bordering Thailand
early last month, according to earlier official report.
</P>
<P>
Nearly six million tablets of methamphetamine stimulant drug
were confiscated in Myanmar-Thai border areas in 1996, according
to Myanmar anti-drug sources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
