<HEADLINE> Fire Rages at Kuala Lumpur International Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The fire that raged at
Terminal One departure hall of the Kuala Lumpur International
Airport in Subang this afternoon has been put out.
</P>
<P>
There were no casualties, airport authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which occurred at 3:30 pm (local time) today, raged
through a section of Terminal One of the airport in Subang, about
30 kilometers from here.
</P>
<P>
Five fire engines rushed to the scene on receiving a distress
call at 3:45 pm and prevented the blaze from spreading to other
sections, a spokesman of the Fire and Rescue Services Department
said, adding 50 firefighters put out the blaze at about 4:00 pm.
</P>
<P>
Flight schedules were not disrupted by the fire.
</P>
<P>
Airport General Manager Haji Abdul Rahman Karim told reporters
that an airport employee on duty spotted smoke billowing at the
entrance of the departure hall A and immediately alerted the fire
and rescue service of the Malaysia Airports Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Another two fire engines from the Royal Malaysia Air Force base
in Subang joined the fire fighting.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is being investigated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
