<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: S. Africa's Population Down; Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's Central
Statistical Service (CSS) announced earlier that by last October
9, the population in the country was estimated about 37.9
million, which is lower than the 1991 official count.
</P>
<P>
The result of the latest census has apparently brought
surprise to many people, who expected the total population in
South Africa should be more than 42 million estimated five years
ago.
</P>
<P>
Some people hailed the result as "good news indeed", saying
the population reduction would undoubtedly alleviate pressure
resulted from over population.
</P>
<P>
According to the United Nations last year, South Africa's
previous estimated population of 42.4 million would have grown to
71 million by 2025.
</P>
<P>
However, based on the new census, South Africa's population
will probably be something less than 65 million by the first
quarter of next century, census experts said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa used to be a country with high fertility rate.
Now, with an annual growth rate that has already been reduced to
22 percent, it is among the slowest growing nations in
sub-Saharan Africa.
</P>
<P>
While satisfied with the current census results, the
authorities have warned that the downgrade of population should
not be used to lull people into false sense of security.
</P>
<P>
There is a great deal to be done, analysts said, not only to
further decelerate growth but to prepare for the growth-related
strains and stresses which assuredly await the country in the
years to come.
</P>
<P>
It has been warned that growing illegal immigrants in South
Africa is making the country experience unprecedented
difficulties in employment, housing and education, etc.
</P>
<P>
South African Home Affairs Minister Mangosutho Buthelezi put
the number recently at five million aliens. But the police
believe that immigrants in the country stand somewhere between
four and nine million.
</P>
<P>
In fact, illegals are still pouring into the country, many
with false documentation, which no doubt has brought the
country's total population well over the 40 million, informed
sources warned.
</P>
<P>
However, the CSS said that despite some inaccuracy, the final
estimate of the total population may differ slightly from the
census result released a fews day ago.
</P>
<P>
The CSS officials also said that the preliminary estimate of
population would be helpful to the central government in
adjustment of financial planning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
