<HEADLINE> U.S. to Train Ugandan Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A team of American green beret
soldiers will train a battalion-size Uganda People's Defense
Forces (UPDF) detachment, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Judy Butterman, director of the United States Information
Service (USIS) in Kampala, confirmed yesterday the report by
"Washington Post" on June 30 and added that the U.S. soldiers
will come in mid-July.
</P>
<P>
The courses in training include relations with noncombatants,
mine detection, water purification and communications.
</P>
<P>
The objective is reportedly to create rapidly deployable
peace-keeping units of eight to ten battalions under the auspices
of the United Nations and the Organization of African Unity,
local newspapers said.
</P>
<P>
Similar training is planned for troops in Senegal, Tunisia,
Ethiopia and Malawi later this year. 
</P>
