<HEADLINE> Fuel Smuggling Rampant in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 100,000 liters of fuel
are being smuggled into Uganda every week, reported the local
daily ''the New Vision'' today.
</P>
<P>
An officer of Ugandan Anti-Smuggling Unit (ASU) who preferred
anonymity was quoted as saying it is the high fue price in Uganda
which is encouraging smuggling.
</P>
<P>
He said a liter of petrol costs 1,140 Uganda Shillings in
Uganda while it costs about 500 Uganda Shillings in neighboring
Kenya where smugglers get it from.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''we are fighting these smugglers but the profit they
make out of the smuggled fuel is so high that they cannot give
up. even if one smuggler loses fuel worth millions of Shillings
he simply calls it bad luck and changes tactics.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that on Monday ASU intercepted 1,140 liters of
petrol at a landing site along the shore of Lake Victoria in
southern Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
