<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to decline
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index fell by another 6.51 points to close at 1,962.4 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased but was still thin at 114.47
million units, worth 270.45 million Singapore dollars (about
189.13 million US dollars). Declines outnumbered advances by 187
to 111, while 324 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Tye Soon was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 13.29 million units. It was followed by the Tianjin
Zhong Xin which had 8.9 million shares traded. Raffles Medical
Group was next with 6.45 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Prime Fund led the gainers of the day as it rose by
1.1 dollars to finish at 11 dollars. Elec gained 40 cents to end
at six US dollars, while Sime Dar closed 34 cents higher at 5.1
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Orchard Parade Hotel was the biggest loser as
it declined by 94 cents to end at 2.4 Singapore dollars. Bukit
Sambawang, Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C), Creative 50 fell by 40 cents
each to close at 26, 14.4, and 24.2 Singapore dollars
respectively. Gentings finished 35 cents lower at 6.45 Singapore
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
