<HEADLINE> Iran Winds up Amphibious Maneuvers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran said here today that it had
wrapped up its four-day amphibious maneuvers in the Persian Gulf
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the units
participating in the military exercises identified the coastal
bunkers and bombed the positions of the hypothetical enemies from
coast and air.
</P>
<P>
The war games were carried out on an area of 1,200 nautical
miles with an aim to upgrade the military and defense readiness of
the Iranian forces in safeguarding the water borders in the
Persian Gulf, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the war games were jointly launched by Iran's
armed forces and the Islamic Revolution's Guards Corps (IRGC).
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not reveal how many forces and what
kind of weapons were involved in the war games.
</P>
<P>
Ground, naval and air units of Iran's revolutionary guards in
late April staged the country's largest Gulf war games, in which
200,000 members of the guards and Basij militia volunteers were
involved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
