<HEADLINE> SADC to Introduce Uniform Driving License </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The 12-nation Southern
African Development Community (SADC) has completed arrangements
to introduce an uniform driving license in the sub-region, SADC
sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The document is to be discussed during a meeting today of SADC
finance and communication ministers in Port Louis, Mauritius,
SADC officials announced from Gaborone, capital of Botswana.
</P>
<P>
The proposal to introduce the license was made by a technical
committee of the Mozambique-based Southern African Transport and
Communication Commission.
</P>
<P>
The SADC groups Angola, Botswana, Lesotho, Malawi, Mauritius,
Mozambique, Namibia, South Africa, Swaziland, Tanzania, Zambia
and Zimbabwe. 
</P>
