<HEADLINE> No Political Strings to Foreign Aid, Urge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Minister of State in the
President's Office for Planning and Investments Ali Juma Shambuna
has urged that donor assistance toward poverty eradication
programs should be unconditional and free from political strings.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here from Zanzibar, opening a
two-day seminar on poverty alleviation whose theme is "Building
government - NGO Alliance in Poverty Alleviation" in the town of
Zanzibar on Wednesday, Shambuna said more support should be
sought to assist in our poverty alleviation projects.
</P>
<P>
He cautioned, however, that such assistance should be given in
good faith and free from any conditions, including political
strings.
</P>
<P>
The minister told the seminar participants, drawn from various
Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs), government departments,
religious leaders, donors and the private sector, that the
Zanzibar Revolutionary Government will continue to give priority
to all poverty eradication programs.
</P>
<P>
He said despite all efforts made so far, poverty was still a
big problem in the Isles.
</P>
<P>
The minister promised that the government would eliminate
hurdles likely to hamper implementation of poverty eradication
programs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he urged all parties involved in the programs to
chart better policies and strategies to ensure success.
</P>
<P>
It was only through collective efforts and through close
cooperation between the government and NGOs that poverty
eradication programs could make any notable achievements, the
minister stressed. 
</P>
