<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgium Offers Grant for Dams in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Belgium has given Kenya a grant of
250 million Shillings (4.63 million U.S. Dollars) for the
construction of dams in arid and semi-arid regions in the eastern
African country.
</P>
<P>
The grant will benefit Makueni, Kajiado and Machakos
districts, today's "Kenya Times" newspaper quoted visiting
Belgian Minister for Development Cooperation Reginald Morees as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Lack of water is a major problem in the third world, said
Morees, adding unless urgent measures are taken, it will overtake
civil strifes within the next 20 years.
</P>
<P>
"Many third world countries are not taking the issue of water
seriously, but we are happy that Kenya has a ministry to deal
with the issue," he told Kenyan Minister for Land Reclamation,
Regional and Water Development Simeon Nyachae on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Molees also promised further technical assistance to Kenya#,
adding that his government is satisfied with the way donor funds
to the country are being utilized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
