<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rapid Growth in Tibet's Township Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The output value of township
enterprises in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region reached
320 million yuan (about 40 million US dollars) last year, up 12.5
percent from the previous year, according to recent statistics.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises produced 161 million kilograms of
vegetables and 1,500 tons of aquatic products last year, official
figures show.
</P>
<P>
To keep the growth of township enterprises the region has taken
steps to lighten their burden and to improve efficiency and their
use of capital. Media coverage has also been given to the
businesses to attract more support for the sector, local officials
say.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises spent 76 million yuan last year to keep
growth up, a nearly 15 percent increase over 1995, and their loan
repayment rate exceeded 80 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation Down in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The general inflationary trend
that has been on the rise in Kenya since the beginning of this
year came down by 4.4 percentage points to 12.8 percent in June
compared with 17.2 percent in May.
</P>
<P>
The underlying inflation in Kenya also dropped from 6.93
percent in May to 4.76 percent in June, according to the lastest
report released by the Central Bank of Kenya (CBK).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the quarterly underlying inflation in the eastern
African country saw a reduction of 1.14 percentage points to 1.44
percent in June, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The current downward trend is caused by the fact that the
January-March severe drought has eased off, the recovery in food
supply following the arrival of rains and the containment of
monetary expansion by the government, said the report.
</P>
<P>
On interest rates, the report revealed that the yield rate on
the government's 91-day Treasury bill fell by 0.25 percentage
points to close at 18.96 from 19.25 the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The average monthly yield on the bills was also lower by 0.91
percent to 19.44 percent last month compared to 20.35 percent the
previous month.
</P>
<P>
However, the lending rates by commercial banks persistently
remain high, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
