<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Massive Park Opens in Shanghai's Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Pudong New Area is not
just a concrete jungle of developments and highways after the
opening of a 100,000 square meter park in its midst, the largest
in the whole of the sprawling city.
</P>
<P>
The park, lying in the center of the Lujiazui Financial and Trade
Zone and surrounded by dozens of newly-built office buildings, is a
veritable lung in the rapidly developing zone on the east side of
the Huangpu River. It is part of city efforts to beautify Pudong
through the creation of green sites within built up areas.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the park is covered by 65,000
square meters of lawns with imported strains of grass dotted with
trees. An 8,600 square meter lake with fountains will
be built in the middle of the park.
</P>
<P>
In its development plan for Pudong New Area, Shanghai has
drawn up regulations requiring the greening of areas surrounding
newly-built residential quarters, factories, and institutions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
