<HEADLINE> New Bridge Across Yangtze River in Southwest China completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 3 (Xinhua) --- A new highway bridge across the
Yangtze River at Wanxian City in the Chongqing Municipality has
been recently completed.
</P>
<P>
The Wanxian Bridge is 856 m long and 24 m wide, and totals
eight km with the approaches. Construction work began on it in May
of 1994. It was completed at a cost of 325 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
It was listed as an important project for helping resettle
people moved because of construction of the Three Gorges Dam and
will play an important role in relocating 800,000 people in
Wanxian City and in providing a thoroughfare east of Chongqing,
the country's fourth and newest municipality, said local officials.
</P>
<P>
Engineers in charge of the construction said that they had
applied cable-stay, beam, and arch technology to this new bridge,
which is 245 m above the water and will allow 10,000-dwt ships to
pass.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng did the calligraphy for the name of the
bridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
