<HEADLINE> South Korea Gains $7 bln Overseas Construction Orders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 3 (Xinhua) -- South Korean construction companies
won a combined 7.12 billion U.S. dollars in contracts from abroad
in the first half of this year, according to the Ministry of
Construction and Transportation.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the contracts represented a 34 percent rise
from a year ago and accounted for 59 percent of the target for the
whole year.
</P>
<P>
The Asian market was the largest source of overseas orders,
amounting to 5.27 billion dollars or 74 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
As for nations, China came first with 1.4 billion dollars,
followed by Indonesia and Singapore with 924 million dollars and
906 million dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Hyundai Company led the list of orders with 2.24 billion
dollars for 16 projects, followed by Daewoo with 2.02 billion
dollars and Samsung with 580 million dollars. 
</P>
