<HEADLINE> S. Africa's PAC Registers Name and Logos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Pan Africanist Congress
(PAC) of South Africa has registered its name as a trademark with
the registrar of trade names in Pretoria, local press said today.
</P>
<P>
PAC General Secretary Mike Muendane was quoted as saying the
move would ensure that disgruntled and expelled members of the
PAC be barred from using the party's symbols.
</P>
<P>
The move would also effectively ensure that former PAC leader,
including its former president Clarence Makwetu not use logos and
phrases protected by the law, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Symbols that may not be used without the mandated authority of
the PAC leadership include the party's logo, its slogans, the
flag and all other distinguishing features and phrases
traditionally associated with the PAC.
</P>
<P>
Muendane said the PAC leadership would fight tooth and nail to
ensure that discredited "elements" within the party not be given
an opportunity to destabilize the organization.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, he warned that the PAC would act ruthlessly
against former members who illegally used the party's symbols.
</P>
