<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tour de France Cycling Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Following are the records from Tour
de France cyclingh race:
</P>
<P>
Most wins: 5 Jacques Anquetil (between 1957 and 1964), Eddy
Merckx (1969-1974), Bernard Hinault (1978-1985), Miguel Indurain
(1991-1995)
</P>
<P>
Previous winners riding this year's Tour: Bjarne Riis (1996)
</P>
<P>
Most stage wins in one Tour: 8 Charles Pelissier (1930), Eddy
Merckx (1970, 1974) and Freddy Maertens (1976)
</P>
<P>
Most stage wins overall: 34 Eddy Merckx
</P>
<P>
Most times on medal podium: 8 Raymond Poulidor (runner-up 3
times, 3rd 5 times) in 14 Tours from 1962 to 1976
</P>
<P>
Most riders to have worn yellow jersey in one Tour: 8 in 1987
</P>
<P>
Most days in yellow jersey: 96 Eddy Merckx (in 7 Tours)
</P>
<P>
Biggest winning margin (since War): 28 minutes 27 seconds
(Fausto Coppi - Stan Ockers in 1952)
</P>
<P>
Smallest winning margin: 8 seconds (Greg LeMond - Laurent
Fignon in 1989)
</P>
<P>
Longest breakaway: 253km Albert Bourlon in 1947
</P>
<P>
Fastest prologue: 55.152 kph Chris Boardman in 1994 over 7.2km
</P>
<P>
Fastest time-trial: 54.545 kph Greg LeMond in 1989 over 24.5km
</P>
<P>
Fastest average stage speed: 49.517 kph Johan Bruyneel in 1993
over 158km
</P>
<P>
Fastest average speed overall: 39.504kph Miguel Indurain in 1992
</P>
<P>
Oldest winner: Firmin Lambot (36) in 1922
</P>
<P>
Youngest winner: Henri Cornet (20) in 1904
</P>
<P>
Most Tours: 16 Joop Zoetemelk between 1970 and 1986 (never
abandoned)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
