<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0207 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy's Telecom, AT&AMP;T to Set up Two Joint Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Telecom of Italy and AT&AMP;T of the
United States today agreed to establish two joint ventures, which
will operate worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Telecom and its subsidiary, STET, will
invest in the AUCS (AT&AMP;T-Unisource Communications Services), a
joint venture of AT&AMP;T and the European telecom giant of Unisource.
</P>
<P>
Telecom-STET will take up at most 30 percent of the AUCS's
shares, according to the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Another 30 percent will go to AT&AMP;T and the rest 40 percent to
Unisource.
</P>
<P>
Telecom and AT&AMP;T will set up another joint venture in Latin
America. Each company takes half of the shares.
</P>
<P>
Telecom, which merged with STET on June 18, is the fifth
largest telecommunications company in the world.
</P>
<P>
Unisource was founded in 1992 by Sweden's TELIA and the
Netherlands' PTT and later joined in by AT&AMP;T and PTT of
Switzerland. It now operates in more than 30 countries and regions
in the world.
</P>
<P>
AT&AMP;T, a telecom giant of the United States, employs 130,000
personnel and its annual trade volume hits 52 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Today's agreement is expected to have strong repercussions in
the world telecommunications market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970703.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Expanding National Industrial Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will have 50 industrial
cooperation projects with other parts of China this year, the
Shanghai Municipal Economic Committee has disclosed.
</P>
<P>
These will involve two billion yuan in investment, with
Shanghai's stake amounting to 51 percent. They are in the
electro-mechanical, textile, metallurgical, building materials,
and chemical industries, and others. The partners are from central
and western parts of the country and the Yangtze River Basin.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has accelerated the pace of cooperating with other
regions in the 1990s while restructuring its industries. In the
past seven years, the municipality has built 1,100 industrial
projects in cooperation with other parts of the country, involving
six billion yuan in spending.
</P>
<P>
The city can produce 2.35 million bicycles, 550,000 TV sets, 52
million batteries, 80,000 tons of detergent, 1.67 million tires,
and 100,000 diesel engines a year in these cooperative
arrangements, with annual sales exceeding four billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Some areas have benefited enormously from the cooperation.
Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, for one,
has been helped by Shanghai in gaining a strong foothold in a
number of industries in more than 80 projects.
</P>
<P>
Officials from Kunming went to Shanghai this May to look for
new partners for 38 major projects. The purpose of their visit was
to explain how to use Kunming's resources, step up development of
quality products, and expand markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
