<HEADLINE> EC Welcomes Report on Euro Impact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC) today
welcomed a report on the impact of a future single European
currency on financial markets.
</P>
<P>
The report, published Wednesday, examines a number of technical
changes needed in the financial markets for the introduction of
Economic and Monetary Union (EMU), scheduled in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The report, prepared by a group of financial experts from
European Union (EU) member states, studies the redenomination of
traded instruments of existing national currencies, market
conventions and benchmarks to meet requests from market
practitioners.
</P>
<P>
The EU commissioners said that it was "evidence of concrete
preparations for the introduction of the euro," and would
facilitate rapid decisions on the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
