<HEADLINE> Garments Exports up in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Garments and textiles
exports climbed by 8.08 percent in the first half this year as the
sector is on track toward a strong recovery tugged by a rebound in
sales to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Exports of apparel, non-apparel and textiles soared by 101.72
million US dollars to 1.36 billion dollars in the first half from
1.26 billion dollars a year ago, local newspaper Philippine Daily
Inquirer reported today.
</P>
<P>
Americans stepped up their purchases by 11.32 percent to 833.64
million dollars in the first six months from 748.89 million
dollars last year, a reversal of its 6 percent drop for the whole
1996.
</P>
<P>
Sales to Canada, another quota country, also surged by 7.7
percent to 26.51 million dollars in the first half from 24.61
million dollars, the Inquirer quoted a report from the Garments
and Textile Export Board as saying.
</P>
<P>
The report also showed sales to non-quota countries inched up
by 5 percent to 308.74 million dollars in the first half from
294.03 million dollars during the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
