<HEADLINE> Poland to Cooperate with Hungary in Joining NATO, EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Polish Prime Minister
Wlodzimierz Cimoszewicz said here today that his country will
increase dialogue with Hungary on joining the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO) and the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
After a meeting with Hungarian Prime Minister Gyula Horn,
Cimoszewicz, who is on a one-day visit, told a press conference
that the two countries have common interests and problems in many
fields especially in seeking the membership of the NATO and the EU.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of Hungary, Poland and the Czech Republic, which have
been chosen by the NATO to become its first new members, will hold
talks in Poland on August 2 to coordinate their positions on
joining the two organizations.
</P>
<P>
Horn said that Slovakia, also one of the four Visegrad
countries, can also meet the basic requirements for joining the
NATO and the EU, and other three Visegrad countries (Poland,
Hungary, Czech Republic) should be helpful on this issue. 
</P>
