<HEADLINE> Fiscal situation in Costa Rica Stable, Says Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican Finance Minister
Francisco de Paula Gutierrez said today that his country's economy
is moving in the right direction but not in a satisfactory way.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the fiscal situation will remain stable
during the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Inflation during the first six months reached 6.5 percent as
against 6.8 percent during the same period last year, Gutierrez
said at a business seminar held by the Costa Rican Chambers' Union.
</P>
<P>
The government expects inflation to grow to 12 percent at the
end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Revenues for the first five months of this year increased by 40
percent over the same period of last year and construction also
expanded, the minister added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, exports grew by 4.4 percent and imports 15.6
percent, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
