<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelans Spend Half Income on Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelans spend on average just
over half their income on food, with some spending up to 72
percent, double the normal average, a Venezuelan market research
company said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure is a sharp rise on the 36 percent registered in the
past, and much higher than the 31 percent the Datanalisis company
said should represent the norm for the proportion of income spent
on food.
</P>
<P>
Housing and services account for 11.58 percent of average
income spending, followed by 11 percent on transport, 4.6 percent
on education and 4.3 percent on health.
</P>
<P>
The survey by Datanalisis also shows that the proportion of the
population falling into the lowest income bracket has risen to 78
percent, with the middle-class falling to 18.5 percent of the
population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
