<HEADLINE> Telecommunication Store Gutted in South Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A fire gutted the store room of the
Hambantota Telecommunication Exchange building in Southern
province of Sri Lanka on Wednesday, according to police sources
here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said over a billion rupee (about 17 million US
dollars) worth of equipment earmarked for the proposed Suriyawewa
Telecommunications project were destroyed by the fire.
</P>
<P>
The fire was extinguished within an hour with the help of the
people in the area.
</P>
<P>
The Ceylon Electricity Board's office at Hambantota has ruled
out the possibility of an electricity leak as the cause of the
sudden fire.  
</P>
