<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Tourism Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital city of south
China's Guangdong Province, received more than 18 million tourists
last year, an increase of 19 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas tourists stood at more than 2.8 million,
a yearly growth of 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
The city earned over 25 billion yuan, accounting for 18 percent
of its GDP in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The city holds its traditional flower fair, lychee fair, dragon
boat fair and lantern fair every year. In addition, it has 26
scenic spots and historic sites.  
