<HEADLINE> Friendship Ties Between Marseilles and North China Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 3 (Xinhua)-- The port of Tianjin just east of
Beijing and the port of Marseilles in France signed a friendship
agreement recently.
</P>
<P>
Marseilles is the eighth foreign port to form a sister-city
agreement with Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Marseilles is the biggest port in France, with a cargo handling
capacity of over 100 million tons annually. Tianjin, which is the
biggest international trade port and transport center in north
China, handles over 60 million tons of goods and 800,000 TEUs
annually.
</P>
<P>
The two ports plan to cooperate in many areas like port
management, port expansion, and shipping. 
</P>
