<HEADLINE> U.S. Names Coach Staff for World Basketball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Los Angeles Lakers coach Del
Harris and college coaches Mike Jarvis and Lon Kruger were named
Wednesday as assistants to US coach Rudy Tomjanovich at the World
Basketball Championships next year.
</P>
<P>
The four-member coaching staff will lead the United States
national team to defend their crown won in Toronto in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Tomjanovich, coach of the two-time National Basketball
Association champion Houston Rockets, was named to coach the NBA
select squad in April.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 world championships, a 16-nation event, will be
contested July 29-August 9 in Athens, Greece. The US and Greek
teams received automatic bids as reigning champion and
host. Fourteen others must qualify.
</P>
<P>
Harris has coached the Lakers the past three years, guiding
them to a 56-26 record, and also led the Milwaukee Bucks and
Houston. He is 489-430 overall in his 11-year NBA coaching career.
</P>
<P>
Jarvis, 229-132, has spent the past seven years at George
Washington University.
</P>
<P>
Kruger just finished his first season at the University of
Illinois with a 22-10 record. He guided the 1995 USA World
University Games and 1991 World Junior Championship teams to
unbeaten championships. 
</P>
