<HEADLINE> Media Say HK's Return Foreshadows Taiwan's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian press today
gave significant coverage of Hong Kong's return to China and
predicted that the historic event foreshadowed Taiwan's future.
</P>
<P>
The El Diario de Brazil newspaper contributed two whole pages
with news and photographs about Hong Kong's return under the
headlines of "Hong Kong's Reunification Should Serve as an Example
for Taiwan" and "China Sends Message to Taiwan."
</P>
<P>
The Message to Taiwan referred to a speech by Chinese President
Jiang Zemin on Tuesday in which he called for concrete steps from
the Taiwan authorities toward national reunification.
</P>
<P>
O Estado de Sao Paulo used its front page and other two pages
to cover the event. One of the headlines read: "Chinese President
Asks for Reunification with Taiwan."
</P>
<P>
The coverage of Hong Kong took up three pages of today's O
Globo, which said Brazil is confident about Hong Kong's
future. The newspaper used four pages Tuesday to report the return
of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
China resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on
Tuesday after 156 years of British colonial rule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
