<HEADLINE> Sweden Beats Spain to Enter Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Sweden edged Spain 1-0 Wednesday
night in Karlskoga to become the first team to reach the
semifinals in the European Women's Soccer Championship.
</P>
<P>
The former champions advanced to the final four due to an own
goal by Spanish defender Judith Corominas six minutes into the
match.
</P>
<P>
Sweden, which beat Russia 2-1 in the Group A opener, has six
points with one game left against France on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Angelique Roujas scored a hat trick as France beat winless
Russia 3-1 at Karlstad, western Sweden. Roujas connected in the
27th, 56th and 74th minutes.
</P>
<P>
Irina Grigorieva notched the only goal for Russia in the 52nd.
</P>
<P>
The Swedes only need a draw against France to win Group A.
</P>
<P>
Norway, which won the 1995 World Championship in Sweden and
finished second behind the United States in Atlanta Olympics,
heads Group B after the first round ahead of defending champion
Germany, Italy and Denmark. 
</P>
