<HEADLINE> North China's Shanxi Province Saw Economy Grow by Nine Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province
expects its GDP to reach 65 billion yuan for the January-June
period, nine percent over the same period last year, according to
the provincial statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau's forecast of its summer grain harvest stands at
3.47 billion kilograms, 3.2 percent higher than its historic
record.
</P>
<P>
For the industrial sector, Shanxi, a coal-rich province,
produced 6.8 percent more goods during the January-May period, but
also enjoyed a sales rate which is nearly three percentage points
above the national average.
</P>
<P>
For the first five months of the year, the province's urban
residents' per capita disposable income witnessed a rise of eight
percent on a yearly basis, amid an easing inflation situation, the
bureau said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
