<HEADLINE> Customs Offices in All Chinese Provincial Capitals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Xining City, the capital of Qinghai
Province in northwest China got approval from the State Council
recently to establish a Customs office.
</P>
<P>
The office building is now under construction and is scheduled
to be completed by June 1998.
</P>
<P>
Xining is the last of provincial capitals in China to open a
customs office, according to official sources.  
