<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Ukraine Marks HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Embassy in Ukraine held a
reception here today to celebrate the return of Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception attended by more than 150 Ukrainian
officials, Ambassador Pan Zhanlin thanked Ukraine for its support
to Hong Kong's return, adding that the return of Hong Kong has won
broad support from the international community.
</P>
<P>
"The political and economic policies, the lifestyle and the
Basic Law will remain unchanged in Hong Kong after July 1," Pan
said. "The Pearl of the East will be much shinier."
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's First Deputy Foreign Minister Anton Buteiko said at
the reception that he was glad to have the chance to congratulate
China on its resuming the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong was a significant success of China's
peaceful foreign policy, Buteiko said. He also expressed the hope
that Ukrainian-Chinese cooperation would be further developed.
</P>
</TEXT>
