<HEADLINE> Siemens Opens Southwest China Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Siemens has opened a
representative office in Chongqing, a newly-established
municipality in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The Chongqing office brings its total number of representative
offices in China to ten. The company's first office in China was
established in Beijing in 1982.
</P>
<P>
Siemens has 35 joint ventures and three wholly-owned companies
in China, employing more than 13,000 workers. Last year, the
company's sales reached 1.9 billion US dollars in the country. A
third of its products sold are produced in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
