<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Prime Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
accepted Prime Minister Pavel Lazarenko's resignation here today,
appointing First Deputy Prime Minister Vasyl Durdynets as acting
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Lazarenko, who became Ukraine's sixth prime minister on May 28
last year, tendered his resignation last Tuesday, saying that he
could not fulfill his duties due to illness.
</P>
<P>
He was hospitalized on June 19 and would have to stay there for
two or three months, but the nature of the sickness was not
specified.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference today, Kuchma said candidate for
the position would be decided after consultations with all the
parties in parliament.
</P>
<P>
Durdynets, once the first deputy parliamentary speaker, was
named deputy prime minister in July 1995 and first deputy prime
minister on June 18, 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
