<HEADLINE> Chinese Embassy in Netherlands Marks HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROTTERDAM, Netherlands, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese embassy
in the Netherlands held a reception Wednesday evening in the Dutch
port city of Rotterdam to celebrate Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 guests, including Dutch government officials,
social dignitaries and Chinese compatriots attended the reception
marking China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong at midnight Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese ambassador to the Netherlands Zhu Manli said that with
the return of Hong Kong, a painful and humiliating page in the
Chinese history, started by the First Opium War in 1840, is now
turned over. 
</P>
</TEXT>
