<HEADLINE> U.S. Condemns Cartoonized Mohammed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The United States on Wednesday
denounced a caricature that mocked Mohammed the founder of Islam,
calling it vulgar and offensive.
</P>
<P>
The founder of Islam was drawn as a pig stomping on the Koran,
the Muslim holy book on a leaflet, which was posted in Hebron over
the weekend by an Israeli woman.
</P>
<P>
"That cartoon is vulgar. It's offensive," State Department
spokesman Nicholas Burns said at a regular briefing.
</P>
<P>
"We want to assure the Palestinian population in Hebron and
throughout the West Bank and Gaza Strip, throughout the Muslim
world, that the United States rejects the offensive, vulgar and
brutal attacks on the religious sensibilities of Muslims," Burns
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"The person who wrote it and the people who support it ought
to be repudiated in the strongest possible terms. It's really
outrageous," he added.
</P>
<P>
According to an Israeli police commander in Hebron, the woman
was arrested and was to be indicted on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
